meanings.definition: To exceed in gross revenue or profit.
meanings.sent1: The new movie managed to outgross all the others at the box office.
meanings.sent2: The popular restaurant chain continues to outgross its competitors in sales.
meanings.sent3: The tiny lemonade stand somehow outgrossed the big coffee shop next door.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to succeed allowed her to outgross even her own expectations.
meanings.sent5: The young entrepreneur's innovative idea helped her outgross the established businesses.

meanings.definition: To surpass in total earnings or sales.
meanings.sent1: The talented musician's album outgrossed all others in the charts.
meanings.sent2: The tech company aims to outgross its previous year's revenue.
meanings.sent3: The friendly neighborhood bakery managed to outgross the big supermarket in cake sales.
meanings.sent4: Her dedication to her craft allowed her to outgross her competitors in the industry.
meanings.sent5: The hardworking team's collaborative effort helped them outgross their quarterly targets.
